claim: Recombinant HA antigens produced using BEVS have been shown to induce significantly higher levels of broadly cross-reactive antibodies against highly conserved regions of HA compared with egg-derived vaccines.
explanation: A table listing four types of influenza vaccines (Egg-based IIV4s, cell culture–based ccIIV4, recombinant RIV4, and live attenuated LAIV4) alongside their labeled contraindications and precautions. does not support the claim because the table only details contraindications and precautions for various vaccine types and contains no immunogenicity or antibody response data.
